###Preparing the Fiddleheads

Fiddleheads <u>SHOULD NEVER</u> be eaten raw.
They must be cooked to release thiaminase which depletes vitamin B.
This enzyme is destroyed by heat, and therefore fiddleheads are perfectly safe when cooked correctly.

