You can find a variety of ways to prepare fiddleheads online.
The way I decided to prepare them was by boiling them.
I rinsed them and then boiled them for 15 minutes, rinsing them one last time after.
While they were boiling they reminded me of green lentils.
The water became dark and discolored while boiling them.
Don't freak out, this is normal.
While these were boiling I cooked up some extra vegetables, quinoa, and tofu with herbs.

Once the fiddleheads were done cooking I set them to the side and then added them into the vegetable stir fry for the last few minutes of cooking so they wouldn't be cold.
Below is a picture of what the fiddleheads looked like after boiling.
You can see that what was left of brown paper-like wrapping completely fell away during the boiling process.

